headline: The RN's unspoken attraction to MAGA – and gradual ideological alignment
description: Like other European nationalists, Marine Le Pen has been put in a tough spot by Donald Trump's imperialist offensive. But the MAGA ideological campaign in Europe, of which France is a key target, has won over her Rassemblement National party over the past year.

Iranians in Turkey flee repression and bear witness to the bloodshed in their country
description: The brutal response of the Iranian regime against protesters has led many Iranians to seek refuge in neighboring Turkey. Their stories attest to the cruelty that the authorities have shown since the beginning of the protest movement.

headline: Tenants are less well-housed than homeowners, says latest INSEE report
description: The 2024 housing conditions survey shows that the proportion of homeowner households (57%) and tenant households (40%) has changed little over the past decade. The latter are more exposed to overcrowding and housing defects.

headline: French say they love art, but rarely visit exhibitions
description: An Ipsos-BVA survey for Beaux Arts Magazine, released on Thursday, reveals the public's taste for contemporary art but a limited knowledge of living artists.

headline: Syria's Al-Hol prison has become a mini-caliphate for IS
description: Since Kurdish guards withdrew from the Al-Hol detention camp, where several thousand jihadists and their families are held, securing the camp has become a major challenge for the Syrian authorities.

How surveillance companies track smartphone users through advertising data
description: Companies are offering law enforcement agencies the ability to track smartphone users through advertising data gathered on their devices. Le Monde attended confidential presentations of these new surveillance tools to learn more.

headline: Who are Greenlanders and what do they really want?
description: Greenland, which is bigger than France, the UK, Germany and Spain combined, has a population of 57,000, most of whom are Inuit. They are also Danish citizens, a legacy of Denmark's colonization of the territory that began in the 18th century.
byline: Arthur Navet ,  Constance Derouin and  Sinead McCausland
